\lim_{n \to +\infty} \frac{2^{n}}{n!}
n \ge 4
0 \le \frac{2^n}{n!} = \prod_{i=1}^n \frac{2}{i} = \frac{2\cdot 2\cdot 2}{1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3} \cdot \prod_{i=4}^n \frac{2}{i} \le \frac{8}{6} \cdot \prod_{i=1}^n \frac{2}{4} = \frac{8}{6 \cdot 2^{n-3}}.
\sum_{i=0}^\infty \frac{2^n}{n!}
\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty} \frac{2^n}{n!} = 0
